Why an Abortion?

Pregnancy is a problem which would have a negative impact on the quality of women's lives and their regular activities. This is particularly true for teenagers who may be in school and could get easily disadvantaged.

Abortion has lots of undesirable side effects that may be detrimental to the health of the mother. According to the website of the Foundation for Scientific Research, "Medical abortion can be a valid and acceptable treatment in a clinical context where safe and legal, but information deficiency is still stunning, risky and even deadly.

Is Abortion Law in Ivory Coast Threatened?

Abortion is restricted within Ivory Coast except in the case of rape, incest or when it is considered necessary to protect the health of the mother.

Anti-abortion bills may pass in the future in Ivory Coast because of the influence of religion on faith based political framework in the nation.
